                            <comment id="13562086" author="yukim" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2013 22:51:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;File#getCannonicalPath returns path after resolving symlinks. Patch instead uses getAbsolutePath so symlinks under data dir works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562101" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2013 22:59:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we cannonicalize both sizes of what we&apos;re comparing, shouldn&apos;t it work either way?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562109" author="yukim" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2013 23:08:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For example, if you have data dir of &quot;/var/lib/cassandra/data&quot; and you symlinked system keyspace under that data dir to &quot;/var/lib/cassandra2/system&quot; as above, cannonicalized paths are &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/var/lib/cassandra/data -&amp;gt; /var/lib/cassandra/data
/var/lib/cassandra/data/system -&amp;gt; /var/lib/cassandra2/system
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thus current comparison doesn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
